name: Sleeping bag cover with hood 2.0
snigelDescription:
A lightweight sleeping bag cover designed to ensure a comfortable night’s sleep for soldiers in any weather and at any location within their sleeping bag.

FEATURES

A light weight sleeping bag cover with a hood and zipped access, to protect your sleeping bag.
Velcro patch by the opening and in the bottom where you can attach a name plate to identify you, so the correct soldier is awakened for duty in the night.
Removable mosquito net attached with a zipper.
Elastic cord around the opening.
Zipper with flaps on the left side.
All seams are taped.

name: Light field blanket 1.0
snigelDescription:
Features:

A light weight blanket to protect against cold, wind and rain.
Updated version which is wider and now has five pressbuttons.

 

The blanket features high loft fleece construction paired with a waterproof and breathable outer fabric.
It serves dual purposes as both a traditional blanket and a insulated poncho worn over the shoulders.
It packs into its own compact bag measuring 19x13x24 cm.
When laid flat, the blanket measures 145 cm in length, 80 cm in width at the foot, and 110 cm at the top.
Ideal for missions lasting 24-48 hours, it effectively wards off cold during rest or guard duty.
Securing it around your shoulders is simple with five press buttons.

 

Download the product sheet:S-53-02172A, Light field blanket 1.0B

1 person

name: Hypothermal bag 1.1
snigelDescription:
A lightweight protection and transport system designed to ensure warmth, ease of examination, treatment, and moveability of wounded soldiers.

FEATURES

Carrying solution rated for 160kg.
Spacious enough to accommodate a wounded soldier wearing a ballistic vest w. pouches
Featuring dual-sided zipper openings for access to all parts of the body while minimizing heat loss.
Crafted with waterproof materials both on the interior and exterior
PU-coating facing the inside, fo cleanability.
Three see-through pockets for triage-card and patient information.
Insulated.
Openablefootbox to make examining and loading easier.

name: I-Bar set -10
snigelDescription:
Features:

The I-Bar is mounted were you want to attach your butt pack, bag or Specialist backpack small.
It can be mounted on any backpack, vest or chest rig.
How to mount it:
Thread the webbing under the band on the platform were you want it to be
The webbing shall be threaded in the direction you want the buckle to face when attached
Pull the webbing through the forward hole on the buckle
Pull the webbing through the back hole on the buckle
Adjust the length of the webbing
Secure the Velcro
Pull the buckle to make sure it is securely attached
Mount the other buckles you need
Attach the bag/Backpack etc and make sure the buckles are placed in the correct positions

This product is packaged in lots of 10 pieces for retailers.

name: Squeeze ballistic front and back 1.3 S2
shopwareName: Squeeze ballistic front and back 1.3 S2
snigelDescription:
The Squeeze ballistic protection and equipment carrying system allows you to adapt the protection and the carrying capacity to meet your needs while taking weight, heat stress and other challenges into account.

The parts can be combined in many different ways depending on the threat, the mission and the environment.

The Squeeze can be carried in a system with the ballistic yoke, small ballistic sleeve set and ballistic groin protection set to make a really good protective set.

The vests in combination with the side panel pouches (84-00984) will fit 90% of the users.
The Squeeze sits very comfortable and tight on your body.
It is easy to adjust in height and width, even when worn.
The closure system with buckle or Velcro slosure is included.
Removable padded shoulder covers with cable channel and elastic loops for antennas.
Your radio ear piece can be placed under a flap in the shoulder cover when not in use.
Foam ridges on the inside for increased ventilation, comfort and lower trauma. Compartments for ballistic panels and ceramic plates on the front and back.
The bottom of the plate carrier is where the ballistic panels and plates are inserted or removed. This is also were you attach the groin protection when needed.
MOLLE webbing on the front and back.
One attachment point on each shoulder for a repair buckle to attach a backpack.
Two attachment points under the MOLLE webbings on the chest for repair buckles to attach the chest panel.
An elastic cord is placed around the edge of the front to hold hydration tubes or cables.
Velcro patches on the front and back for name and unit patches.

The product includes the following components:

Front carrier.
Back carrier.
Left and right shoulder cover.
Buckle closure
Velcro closure
Front plackard.

Note: The side panels, belt, yoke and groin protection are NOT included.

Size guide:

The vest including side panel pouches can be adjusted 30 cm in width. Select the side panel pouches according to your waist measurement with clothes:

	Side panel size 7 min	Side panel size 7 max	Side panel size 9 min	Side panel size 9 max	Side panel size 11 min	Side panel size 11 max
						
Squeeze 2	95	121	111	137	127	164
